.8 as well as updates to the Android designer: <a href=\"http://msft.social/kAKmQv\" target=\"_blank\">[msft.social]</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/VisualStudio/status/1015265917373239296/photo/1\" target=\"_blank\">[twitter.com]</a></p><p class=\"tweet\" data-status-id=\"1015025809600311300\"><a href=\"https://t.co/NnCC3iFhHa\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Matt Bierner [mattbierner]\" src=\"https://songhay.blob.core.windows.net:443/shared-social-twitter/mattbierner.jpg\" /></a> Just published a <a href=\"http://twitter.com/@code\" target=\"_blank\">@code</a> extension that lets you add embedded language syntax highlighting to <a href=\"http://twitter.com/search?q='%23javascript\" target=\"_blank\">#javascript</a> or <a href=\"http://twitter.com/search?q='%23typescript\" target=\"_blank\">#typescript</a> tagged template strings with a /*language*/ comment <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=bierner.comment-tagged-templates\" target=\"_blank\">[marketplace.visualstudio.com]</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/mattbierner/status/1015025809600311296/photo/1\" target=\"_blank\">[twitter.com]</a></p><p class=\"tweet\" data-status-id=\"1015836918557302800\"><a href=\"https://t.co/7KvH8Bz1QN\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Minko Gechev [mgechev]\" src=\"https://songhay.blob.core.windows.net:443/shared-social-twitter/mgechev.jpg\" /></a> A standard for documenting TypeScript by <a href=\"http://twitter.com/@Microsoft\" target=\"_blank\">@Microsoft</a> üë∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Designed for TypeScript üîì Open standard üìù Markdown integration\n            üí™ Extensible It's definitely worth checking out at <a href=\"https://github.com/Microsoft/tsdoc\" target=\"_blank\">[github.com]</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/mgechev/status/1015836918557302784/photo/1\" target=\"_blank\">[twitter.com]</a></p><p class=\"tweet\" data-status-id=\"1015169981368225800\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Martijn_Cuppens\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Martijn Cuppens [Martijn_Cup