=\"_blank\">[twitter.com]</a></p><p class=\"tweet\" data-status-id=\"1015022357264547800\"><a href=\"http://t.co/UNdqV0Z1zz\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Bryan D. Wilhite [BryanWilhite]\" src=\"https://songhay.blob.core.windows.net:443/shared-social-twitter/BryanWilhite.jpeg\" /></a> ‚ÄúWhy you should not use Google Cloud.‚Äù by <a href=\"http://twitter.com/@serverpunch\" target=\"_blank\">@serverpunch</a><a href=\"https://medium.com/@serverpunch/why-you-should-not-use-google-cloud-75ea2aec00de\" target=\"_blank\">[medium.com]</a></p><p class=\"tweet\" data-status-id=\"1015374905330659300\"><a href=\"http://t.co/UNdqV0Z1zz\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Bryan D. Wilhite [BryanWilhite]\" src=\"https://songhay.blob.core.windows.net:443/shared-social-twitter/BryanWilhite.jpeg\" /></a> Microsoft Azure launches tamper-proof Azure Immutable Blob Storage\n            for financial services <a href=\"https://azure.microsoft.com/blog/microsoft-azure-launches-tamper-proof-azure-immutable-blob-storage-for-financial-services/\" target=\"_blank\">[azure.microsoft.com]</a></p><p class=\"tweet\" data-status-id=\"1015375304569729000\"><a href=\"http://t.co/UNdqV0Z1zz\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Bryan D. Wilhite [BryanWilhite]\" src=\"https://songhay.blob.core.windows.net:443/shared-social-twitter/BryanWilhite.jpeg\" /></a> .NET Core Microservices ‚Äì DShop <a href=\"http://piotrgankiewicz.com/2018/07/05/net-core-microservices-dshop/\" target=\"_blank\">[piotrgankiewicz.com]</a></p><p class=\"tweet\" data-status-id=\"1016394566608384000\"><a href=\"https://t.co/yiRiDd0Ocv\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Jamie-Presenting Nipples üè≥Ô∏è‚Äçüåà [jamiebuilds]\" src=\"https://songhay.blob.core.windows.net:443/shared-social-twitter/jamiebuilds.jpg\" /></a> Oh well this was a fun adventure. Recommendation: Don't use `+=\n            await` or `-= await`, they store the initial value eagerly, and if\n            that value gets updated while await-ing, it will get overwritten. <a href=\